    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Deuteronomy 1<supplied reason="lost">9</supplied></title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut019-P312r-L9_trl" n="9"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.005.018.trl.xml#Deut018-P312r-L9_trl" />
                        <l n="1">When
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             the Lord your God will drive away the kingdoms whose
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             land the Lord your God is giving you, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             you will inherit them, and you will dwell in their cities and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             in their houses,</l>
                        <l n="2">You shall set apart three cities
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             for you in the midst of your land which the Lord your God gives
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             you to inherit it.</l>
                        <l n="3">You shall smoothen you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             a way and divide into three parts the border of your land that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             the Lord your God will give you for inheritance, and it shall be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             for any murderer to flee there.</l>
                        <l n="4">And this is the case of the murderer,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             who shall flee there and live: If anyone kills his fellow
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             without knowing, and he was not his enemy
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             for long,</l>
                        <l n="5">and if a man comes with his fellow
                            <milestone unit="page" n="312v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             into the forest to cut wood, and his hand is reached out with the axe
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             to cut down the tree, and the iron comes off the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             wood and finds his fellow, and he dies: he shall flee
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             to one of those cities, and live,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="6">Lest the avenger of blood will pursue after
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             the murderer, while his heart grows warm and will catch up with him
                            because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             the way is much<ref n="1" target="#Deut-019-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor"
                             />, and he smites him until his soul leaves |him|, whereas
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             he has no sentence of death, because he was not an enemy
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             to him for a long.</l>
                        <l n="7">On account of this I command
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             you, saying, “You shall set apart three cities for you.”</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                        <l n="8">And if the Lord your God will widen
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             your border, as he has sworn to your fathers, and will give you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             all the land which he promised to give to your fathers,</l>
                        <l n="9">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             If you keep all these commandments to do them, which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             I command you today, to love the service of Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             your God and to walk in his ways every day,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             then you shall add three more cities for you, to these
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             three.</l>
                        <l n="10">So innocent blood will not be spilled
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             in the midst of your land that the Lord your God is giving you for an
                            inheritance,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             and the guilt of blood would be on you.</l>
                        <l n="11">But if
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             there is a man who is an enemy to his fellow and lies in wait for him
                            and
                            <milestone unit="page" n="313r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             rises up against him and smites him until his soul leaves |him|,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             and he dies, and he flees to one of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             these cities,</l>
                        <l n="12">Then the elders of his city shall send and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             take him from there and give him to the hand of the avenger
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             of blood, so he will die.</l>
                        <l n="13">Your eye shall not pity him,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             but you shall drive away the guilt of innocent blood from Israel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             and it will be good for you.</l>
                        <l n="14">You shall not move your neighbour’s border
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             that the first ones set, in your inheritance which you shall inherit
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             in the land that the Lord your God is <supplied reason="lost"
                                >giving</supplied> you to inherit
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             it.</l>
                        <l n="15">One witness shall not rise up against a man for any
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             iniquity or for any sin, in any sin that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             he sins. According to the word of two witnesses or
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             according to the word of three witnesses shall the matter be
                            established.</l>
                        <l n="16">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             If a sinful witness rises up against any man to testify
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             against him a word of trespass,</l>
                        <l n="17">And the two
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             men who have the trial shall stand before the Lord,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             before the priests and the judges who shall be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             in that time,</l>
                        <l n="18">And the judges shall inquire well,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             and, lo, if the witness is a false witness and has
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             testified falsely against his <delSpan spanTo="#Deut-019-del001_trl"
                                 />fellow<anchor type="delSpan" xml:id="Deut-019-del001_trl" />
                            <addSpan spanTo="#Deut-019-add001_trl" /><emph>brother</emph><anchor
                                type="addSpan" xml:id="Deut-019-add001_trl" />,</l>
                        <l n="19">Then
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             you shall do to him as he had thought to do to his brother.
                            <milestone unit="page" n="313v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             So shall you drive the evil away from among you.</l>
                        <l n="20">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             those who remain shall hear and fear, and they shall not continue
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             to do anything like this bad thing among you.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="21">And your eye shall not pity: life for life,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand,
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut019-P313v-L6_trl" n="6"
                                next="ADub.III.73.005.020.trl.xml#Deut020-P313v-L6_trl" />
                             foot for foot. </l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
